<p>The shortcut to the hypothesis testing of the Wilcoxon signed rank-test =
is knowing the critical z-value for a 95% confidence interval (or a 5% leve=
l of significance) which is z =3D 1.96 for a two-tailed test and directiona=
lity.&nbsp; Whenever a test is based the normal distribution the sample z v=
alue needs to be 1.96 or higher to reject the null hypothesis.</p>



